node34.1: * Only hospitalizations with available reason types are included.  * Incidental hospitalizations are those where a COVID-positive person has been hospitalized but their reason for admission was deemed to be unrelated to their COVID diagnosis.  * For recent hospital admissions, there may be a delay in reason type information.
